p :::s10:::When Montag fails to show up for work , his fire chief , Beatty , pays a visit to his house .
:::s15:::Beatty tells Montag to take twenty-four hours or so to see if his stolen books contain anything worthwhile and then turn them in for incineration .
:::s29:::Montag goes to the fire station and hands over one of his books to Beatty .
n :::s30:::Beatty confuses Montag by barraging him with contradictory quotations from great books .
n :::s34:::Beatty forces Montag to burn the house himself ; when he is done , Beatty places him under arrest .
n :::s35:::When Beatty continues to berate Montag , Montag turns the flamethrower on his superior and proceeds to burn him to ashes .
n :::s37:::The Mechanical Hound , a monstrous machine that Beatty has set to attack Montag , pounces and injects Montag 's leg with a large dose of anesthetic .
